    title_en:'Obtaining Health Coverage from the Ministry of Public Health (Approval for Outpatient Treatment or Admission to a Private Hospital at the Ministry\'s Expense)',
    ministry_en:'Ministry of Public Health',
    description_en:'',
    requiredDocuments_en:['Detailed standard medical report including the date of admission, the hospital\'s stamp, the physician\'s stamp and signature with their syndicate membership number, and the phrase "at the expense of the Ministry of Public Health."','Original individual civil status extract together with a copy thereof, which must bear the applicant\'s photograph if aged over five years; a birth certificate for a newborn not yet recorded on the civil status extract; and, for naturalized persons, the relevant supplement of the Official Gazette pertaining to the naturalization must be presented.','Written undertaking from the patient stating that they are not benefiting from the Civil Servants Cooperative, the Army, the Gendarmerie (Internal Security Forces), or any other guarantor entity.','Certificate from the National Social Security Fund confirming that the patient is not benefiting from health coverage under Social Security, provided that the certificate is not more than two months old.'],
    fees_en:'No fee is due',
